# Kombu Dashi:
15g kombu for 1L water, steep 3hrs room temperature or overnight in the fridge, don't wipe it beforehand, do cut slits in it
Freeze the kombu after, use it for Tsukudani (simmer in 1cup water/dashi, 1Tbsp mirin and sake each, 1tsp rice vinegar, 2Tbsp soy, 1tsp sugar, some dashi, 1tsp chili powder until liquid reduces)

# Seasoned rice:
Prepare 2 cups rice, but with 2Tbsp soy, 2Tbsp mirin, 1Tbsp sake, liquid from soaking dried mushrooms, and dashi to top off. Throw in the soaked mushrooms before starting the rice cooker
